cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and combinatorial algorithms, which are the main topics of cs.CG. The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (data structures) and cs.NA (numerical analysis). The use of combinatorial techniques and the study of partitions and intersections of convex hulls suggest that it could also belong to cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.GT (graph theory).
